nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As to whether North bid 5@C over 4@H as a sacrifice, knowing he would be going down, the answer is yes. At this vulnerability I would bid 5@C. If I have 7 clubs, which I usually do, that gives us an 11 card fit and it is unlikely we are beating 4 hearts. In fact, if North wanted to bid 5@C over 3@H that would be a reasonable tactic. That makes it harder for the opponents to guess what to do. I personally would have either passed with the North hand or bid 5@C.|
